        <h2>Chitradurga</h2>

        <p>A massive fort with historical significance and scenic views.</p>

        <p>Chitradurga Fort is a sprawling fortress, offering a glimpse into Karnataka’s medieval history.</p>

        <img src="https://backpackrkl.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/dsc_92961-01.jpg?w=1400" alt="Chitradurga">
       
        <p>Chitradurga, located in Karnataka, is known for its historical significance, especially the Chitradurga Fort, which dates back to the 17th century. The fort, with its walls, temples, and gates, attracts many visitors. The city is surrounded by scenic hills and lakes and is home to temples like the Virupaksha Temple. It plays a key role in the region’s agriculture, producing crops like groundnuts and sunflower. Rich in Kannada culture, Chitradurga blends tradition with modern life, serving as a key transit point between Bangalore and Hubli.</p>
       
